===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{m|la|trigonometria}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|τρίγωνον||triangle}} + {{m|la|-metria||-metry}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|~|trigonometries}}

# {{lb|en|mathematics}} The branch of [[mathematics]] that deals with the [[relationship]]s between the [[side]]s and the [[angle]]s of [[triangle]]s and the [[calculation]]s based on them, particularly the [[trigonometric function]]s.

